Reasoning: The paper discusses mapping techniques for analyzing citation relations among journals in the Arts & Humanities Citation Index (A&HCI). This involves using visualization techniques to explore the cognitive structure of the A&HCI and identifying subsets of journals based on citation patterns. The paper also discusses options for validation, including comparing results with institutional organization. This work involves elements of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), social and information networks (cs.SI), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
